results.name: Number of divisors of A036035(n,k).
link: Alois P. Heinz, Rows n = 0..30, flattened
Byungchul Cha et al., An Investigation on Partitions with Equal Products, arXiv:1811.07451 [math.NT], 2018.
example: Express A036035(n,k) by its prime signature; add one to each exponent, then multiply: 180 = (2^2)*(3^2)*(5^1) therefore the number of divisors is (2+1)*(2+1)*(1+1)= 18
As an irregular triangle, whose n-th row has A000041(n) terms, sequence begins:
program: (PARI) tabf(nn) = {for (n=1, nn, forpart(p=n, print1(prod(k=1, #p, (1+p[k])), ", ")); print(););} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Nov 11 2015
